5 on page 18, lines 25-26, by inserting between the lines the following:
6
7 "SALE OF MAINFRAME AND RELATED TECHNOLOGY COMPONENTS
8 SECTION 5.1. Notwithstanding Article 3A of Chapter 143 of the General Statutes,
9 G.S. 143-49(4), or any other law pertaining to surplus State property, the Administrative Office
10 of the Courts may sell its mainframe computing system and any related components on terms
11 that the Administrative Office of the Courts deems to be in its best interest without involvement
12 by the State Surplus Property Agency designated in G.S. 143-64.01 and without being required
13 to pay any service charge or surcharge to the State Surplus Property Agency. The net proceeds
14 of this sale shall be deposited in the Court Information Technology Fund established by
15 G.S. 7A-343.2.
16
17 REMOTE PUBLIC ACCESS FEES
18 SECTION 5.2. G.S. 7A-109(d) reads as rewritten:
19 "(d) In order to facilitate public access to the electronic data processing records or any
20 compilation of electronic court records or data of the clerks of superior court, except where public
21 access is prohibited by law, the Director may enter into one or more nonexclusive contracts under
22 reasonable cost recovery terms with third parties to provide remote electronic access to the
23 electronic data processing records or any compilation of electronic court records or data of the
24 clerks of superior court by the public. Neither the Director nor the Administrative Office of the
25 Courts is the custodian of the records of the clerks of superior court or of the electronic data
26 processing records or any compilation of electronic court records or data of the clerks of superior
27 court. CostsFunds recovered pursuant to this subsection shall be remitted to the State Treasurer
28 to be held in the Court Information Technology Fund established in G.S. 7A-343.2."".
